# 2 · Opportunity

`[Visual: one bold data graphic. Suggested angle: “25 fridge opens / day × 0 brands owned,” or kitchen attention heat map highlighting the fridge as a high-frequency attention zone.]`

Only FridgeChannel does all three at once:

**01 — No algorithm, no AI summary, no ad blockers**
A hardware-native, in-home touchpoint. No Meta volatility, no Google policy whiplash, no AI stripping context, no blockers. Nike controls the surface.

**02 — 25+ daily household impressions without interrupting life**
US homes open the fridge ~20–40 times per day. Each open is a visible brand moment—~25,000 annualized impressions per household. Frequency digital rarely matches at this cost; physical presence apps cannot copy.

**03 — Household reach, cross-generational**
Unlike a phone or earbuds, the fridge is shared. One device reaches kids choosing sports, parents buying gear, and grandparents absorbing brand cues. Few channels are truly “household-native.”

> **FridgeChannel is the only household-scale media surface: it can’t be filtered, skipped, or easily cloned. Nike can test and own this daily media surface before competitors notice.**

